Abu Dhabi’s Royal Capital Fund Gets First S&P Rating in Mideast

-- B y   D a n a   E l   B a l t a j i
-- 
2011-06-13T08:15:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/abu-dhabi-s-royal-capital-fund-gets-first-s-p-rating-in-mideast.html
A fixed income fund by Royal Capital
PJSC, an Abu Dhabi-based investment bank, was assigned an A
grade, the lowest rating by Standard & Poor’s Fund Services, S&P
said in a statement dated today.  The  Royal Capital Mena Fixed Income Plus (ROYCMFI)  Fund was also
given a bond fund volatility rating of V5, according to the
statement. The fund, which is benchmarked against the
HSBC/Nasdaq  Middle East  Aggregate Bond index, said it’s the
first in the Middle East to get an S&P rating.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Dana El Baltaji in Dubai 
 delbaltaji@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net . 